{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"76c90d41-445e-4820-a202-1cfbeb755cbc","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Framework support dropped in MSTest v3:**\n\n| Target | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped (EOL) |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped (EOL) |\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** on the .NET (Core) side. Two of your three target frameworks (`net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1`) are no longer supported.\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to replace those targets with supported ones, e.g.:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net6.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n```\n\nor target `net8.0` for the latest LTS. You can also consolidate the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` / `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages into the single **`MSTest`** meta-package in v3.\n\nWant me to update the project file for the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e194185d-04f1-4023-94ad-b116621041ce","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nKey compatibility issues with MSTest v3:\n\n1. **Dropped framework support**: MSTest v3 dropped support for older target frameworks. Specifically:\n   - `net462` — MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET Framework 4.6.2, so `net462` should still be supported. Actually, let me think more carefully. MSTest v3 minimum is .NET Framework 4.6.2, so `net462` is the minimum and should work.\n   - `netcoreapp3.1` — MSTest v3 dropped support for .NET Core 3.1 (it's out of support). MSTest v3 requires at least .NET 6.0 for the .NET Core/.NET side.\n   - `net5.0` — .NET 5.0 is also out of support and not supported by MSTest v3.\n\n2. **Package consolidation**: MSTest v3 consolidates the test framework and adapter into a single package, simplifying the dependency structure compared to v2.\n\nThe core compatibility issues are that MSTest v3 requires .NET Framework 4.6.2 or higher and .NET 6.0 or higher, which means `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` are both blockers. The `net462` target should work fine since it meets the minimum framework requirement.\n\nThe user needs to migrate those older target frameworks to `net6.0` or `net8.0` to resolve the immediate issue, though there are also some breaking API changes in MSTest v3 worth being aware of.","outputTokens":858,"requestId":"4C23:59E9:2A062B:314B12:6A01428B"},"id":"3e511c13-f21d-4147-bc3d-2db47e6ab05f","timestamp":"2026-05-11T02:44:45.394Z","parentId":"0f4a7cb3-25aa-4064-aef4-7bf45ef63179"}
